# Services API Testing
# Use with REST Client extension in VS Code

### 1. Get all services (with pagination)
GET http://localhost:3000/api/services?page=1&limit=10

### 2. Create new service (auto-generated slug)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/services
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Green Architecture Design",
  "image_url": "https://example.com/green-architecture.jpg",
  "description": "Eco-friendly architecture design service using recycled materials and energy-efficient solutions."
}

### 3. Create service with custom slug
POST http://localhost:3000/api/services
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Solar Energy Consulting",
  "slug": "solar-energy-consulting",
  "image_url": "https://example.com/solar-energy.jpg",
  "description": "Consulting and design services for residential and commercial solar energy systems."
}

### 4. Get service by ID (replace 1 with actual ID)
GET http://localhost:3000/api/services/1

### 5. Get service by slug
GET http://localhost:3000/api/services/slug/green-architecture-design

### 6. Update service (replace 1 with actual ID)
PUT http://localhost:3000/api/services/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Green Architecture Design - Updated",
  "slug": "green-architecture-design-updated",
  "image_url": "https://example.com/green-architecture-updated.jpg",
  "description": "Updated eco-friendly architecture design service with new features and enhanced sustainability solutions."
}

### 7. Delete service (replace 1 with actual ID)
DELETE http://localhost:3000/api/services/1

### 8. Test validation - Create service without name (should fail)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/services
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "description": "Service without name"
}

### 9. Test validation - Create service with duplicate slug (should fail if exists)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/services
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Test Service",
  "slug": "green-architecture-design"
}